					Posts: 2,130
					
				</div>
				<div>   </div>
			</div>					
		
	</td>
	<td class="alt2">
	
		
		
		<!-- message -->
		<div>Well, the thing is, mobs in EQ (and most other mmog's) dont really have any AI... they have basic scripts, with little adaptiveness and no learning ability.  A real Mob AI would learn and adapt to whatever strategies a player came up with.  Such a thing, though, was WELL beyond what was technologically possible when EQ was released (and probably even today.)<br />
<br />
However, it's been suggested many times that they give at least *some* mobs an advanced real AI system, like bosses and such.  At least that way they would be more than the standard "figure out the trick, then proceed to farm" that they have been for 5 years.</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
		
		
	
	</td>
</tr>
